Setting up a Strimzi Kafka Cluster Operator
    1) Create a namespace (recommended and didn't work on default-NS)
        kubectl create namespace kafka

    2.1) Download cluster operator yaml (version 0.21.1 (latest at the moment))
        curl -L https://github.com/strimzi/strimzi-kafka-operator/releases/download/0.21.1/strimzi-cluster-operator-0.21.1.yaml \
        | sed 's/namespace: .*/namespace: kafka/' \
        | kubectl apply -f - -n kafka

    2.2) Setups standard persistent storage class (CSI Driver)
        // Each ZooKeeper and Broker gets 10GB (In total 9 pods = 90GB)
        kubectl apply -f kafka/gce_standard_storageclass.yaml -n kafka
      
    2.3) Setup Kafka Instances(Brokers)
        IF storage type == JBOD:
            JBOD increases data storage for Kafka Brokers and improves performance
        kubectl apply -f kafka/kafka-instance.yaml --namespace kafka


Useful Commands:
    kubectl get pods --all-namespaces
    kubectl logs strimzi-cluster-operator-77d77c7479-tmv6z --namespace kafka


    Producer example:
        kubectl -n kafka run kafka-producer -ti \
        --image=quay.io/strimzi/kafka:0.21.1-kafka-2.7.0 \
        --rm=true --restart=Never -- bin/kafka-console-producer.sh \
        --broker-list kafka-cluster-kafka-bootstrap:9092 \
        --topic my-topic

    Consumer example:
        kubectl -n kafka run kafka-consumer -ti \
        --image=quay.io/strimzi/kafka:0.21.1-kafka-2.7.0 \
        --rm=true --restart=Never -- bin/kafka-console-consumer.sh \
        --bootstrap-server kafka-cluster-kafka-bootstrap:9092 \
        --topic my-topic \
        --from-beginning


